{"source_key":"sha256-852da461b9759bc2736926d9891eb9a3","record_index":9868,"record_hash":"sha256:ac10681824780cd25069085c0987478037b56241237747e3080ad72526c4a6da","timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:34:49.687Z","kind":"tool_result","source_event_kind":"codex:response_item:function_call_output","role":null,"text":"{\"status\":{\"[REDACTED:entropy]\":{\"completed\":\"Best prior art: **Claude Code for local session UX**, **Copilot CLI for remote/cross-device continuity**, **Cursor/Windsurf for lightweight “pull past context into this chat”**, and **Aider for simple file-based history**.\\n\\n**Claude Code**\\nSource: [Manage sessions](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/sessions), [How Claude Code works](https://code.claude.com/docs/en/how-claude-code-works)\\n\\n- `claude --continue`: resume most recent session in current directory.\\n- `claude --resume`: open picker.\\n- `claude --resume <name>` / `<session-id>`: direct resume.\\n- `/resume`: switch from inside an active session.\\n- `--from-pr <number>`: resume session linked to a PR.\\n- `/rename`, `claude -n`: name sessions.\\n- `/branch` or `--fork-session`: fork a conversation without mutating original history.\\n- Picker can widen from current worktree to all repo worktrees or all projects on machine.\\n- Shows session name/summary, age, message count, branch, project path.\\n- `/clear`, `/compact`, `/context`: manage context window.\\n- `/export`: export transcript; JSONL stored locally under `~/.claude/projects/...`.\\n\\nGitButler should copy: named sessions, branch/worktree-aware picker, fork-vs-resume distinction, PR-linked resume, previewable transcripts, and explicit local storage/export.\\n\\n**OpenAI Codex**\\nSources: [openai/codex repo](https://github.com/openai/codex), [ChatGPT release notes: Codex remote access](https://help.openai.[REDACTED:entropy])\\n\\nFrom local `codex-cli 0.121.0 --help`:\\n\\n- `codex resume [SESSION_ID] [PROMPT]`: resume by UUID or thread name.\\n- `codex resume --last`: most recent.\\n- `codex resume --all`: disables cwd filtering and shows CWD column.\\n- `codex resume --include-non-interactive`: includes `exec` sessions.\\n- `codex fork [SESSION_ID] [PROMPT]`: fork previous interactive session.\\n- `--remote <ws/wss>`: connect TUI to remote app server.\\n- `codex cloud`: browse cloud tasks and apply changes loca\n[TRUNCATED]\n[Claude context editing](https://platform.claude.[REDACTED:entropy])\\n\\n   **Implication:** when trimming transcript/tool output, write a provenance-backed summary first. Never silently drop tool results that affect next actions.\\n\\n9. **Research points toward structured, provenance-aware memory.**  \\n   Recent work argues memory is a write-manage-read loop, not a blob of chat history. Memori frames memory as compact structured triples/summaries; MemLineage adds provenance/lineage to prevent untrusted memories from later justifying sensitive actions.  \\n   Sources: [Memory for Autonomous LLM Agents survey](https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.07670), [Memori](https://arxiv.org/abs/2603.19935), [MemLineage](https://arxiv.org/abs/2605.14421)\\n\\n   **Implication:** every remembered fact should carry source, timestamp, author/agent, confidence, and derivation. Treat memory from tool output, user instruction, and model inference differently.\\n\\n**Recommended CLI Design**\\n\\nUse this shape:\\n\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"handoff_id\\\": \\\"uuid\\\",\\n  \\\"thread_id\\\": \\\"stable-session-id\\\",\\n  \\\"checkpoint_id\\\": \\\"monotonic-or-content-addressed-id\\\",\\n  \\\"created_at\\\": \\\"timestamp\\\",\\n  \\\"from_agent\\\": \\\"agent-id\\\",\\n  \\\"to_agent\\\": \\\"optional-agent-id\\\",\\n  \\\"goal\\\": \\\"what we are trying to finish\\\",\\n  \\\"state\\\": {\\n    \\\"status\\\": \\\"in_progress | blocked | ready_for_review\\\",\\n    \\\"next_action\\\": \\\"single concrete next step\\\",\\n    \\\"open_questions\\\": [],\\n    \\\"risks\\\": []\\n  },\\n  \\\"artifacts\\\": {\\n    \\\"transcript_ref\\\": \\\"path-or-uri\\\",\\n    \\\"summary_ref\\\": \\\"path-or-uri\\\",\\n    \\\"tool_log_ref\\\": \\\"path-or-uri\\\",\\n    \\\"workspace_diff_ref\\\": \\\"path-or-uri\\\"\\n  },\\n  \\\"provenance\\\": {\\n    \\\"commands_run\\\": [],\\n    \\\"files_read\\\": [],\\n    \\\"files_changed\\\": [],\\n    \\\"external_sources\\\": []\\n  }\\n}\\n```\\n\\nMy take: build the durable source of truth as an append-only local event/checkpoint log, then generate compact handoff summaries from it. Summaries are convenient; logs are truth.\"}},\"timed_out\":false}","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T18:34:49.687Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"function_call_output","call_id":"[REDACTED:entropy]"}}}